                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "I tried making one once and yeah, its really hard mapping the polar look to mouse. I just did the up or right for +ve and it just seems wrong when its at certain angles. If you do a drag it can be really sensitive to the singularity that exists near the center which is where you naturally start a drag  so its pretty interesting you are removing that singularity with a local center of rotation. How are you tracking that?\n"
